# RentChill Core Development Rules

## 1. Architecture (Separation of Concerns)
- Strictly separate Logic from UI. 
- Business logic, database calls, and state management must reside in `src/hooks/` or `src/services/`.
- UI components (`src/components/`) must be "dumb" presentation layers (Headless UI pattern).

## 2. Coding Standard
- Use Next.js App Router, React Server Components where possible, and Tailwind CSS.
- Follow the "Less is More" philosophy. Eliminate redundant code. Complexity is the enemy.
- Do not generate graphical assets or images unless explicitly requested.
- Always prioritize precision, readability, and performance.

## 3. Communication
- All prompts and technical instructions provided to Cursor Composer/Chat will be in English.
